## Early game

**Akkad** on Eris (Defense, Infested Ship tileset, levels 35-45) is thick with
Spore Culture containers — the glowing Infested pods that reliably burst into
Nano Spores when destroyed. Clearing the first few Defense waves is enough to
break several of them, and because these are container pickups rather than
enemy drops, Resource Drop Boosters and the Steel Path passive don't affect
the yield here.

## Mid & late game

**Piscinas** on Saturn (Dark Sector Survival, Grineer Asteroid tileset, levels
26-36) is the best per-hour spot once a squad can run Steel Path: the Dark
Sector's resource-chance bonus plus Infested enemy density means a Nekros or
Khora in the squad meaningfully boosts the haul by re-rolling extra drops on
top of what the mission caches already provide. Long Survival rotations
outperform resetting the mission, since Nano Spores accumulate quickly the
longer you stay.

